The paper deals with the problem of finding maximum flow in temporal networks, which involves analyzing the structure and dynamics of networks over time. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper focuses on algorithmic and computational aspects of the problem, cs.DS and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SI, cs.LG, and cs.IT.
